    skos:definition "In a chemical reaction context, compound preparation is an act of artifact processing during which a compound (i.e. a component of a reaction) is prepared (e.g. dried, repurified) for a reaction. This step is frequently necessary as many compounds from suppliers are not in desired conditions for a reaction."@en ;
