    skos:altLabel "Portion Of Tool Steel" ;
    skos:definition "Any Iron alloy that has various carbon steels and alloy steels that are particularly well-suited to be made into tools and tooling. They fall into 6 properties: water-hardening, cold-work, shock-resistant, high-speed, hot-work, and special purpose. These are known also by their series W, O, A, D, S, T, M, H, P, L, and F [Merriam-Webster]"@en ;
    mds:hasDomain "Charact" ;
    mds:hasStudyStage "Sample" ;
